theorem interior_diff_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hB : IsClosed (B : Set X)) :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) = interior A \ B := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A :=
      (interior_mono (Set.diff_subset : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
    have hx_notB : x ∉ B := by
      have hxAB : x ∈ A \ B := interior_subset hx
      exact hxAB.2
    exact ⟨hx_intA, hx_notB⟩
  · rintro ⟨hx_intA, hx_notB⟩
    rcases mem_interior.1 hx_intA with ⟨U, hUsub, hUopen, hxU⟩
    have hVopen : IsOpen (U \ B : Set X) := hUopen.diff hB
    have hVsub : (U \ B : Set X) ⊆ A \ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨hUsub hy.1, hy.2⟩
    have hxV : x ∈ U \ B := ⟨hxU, hx_notB⟩
    exact mem_interior.2 ⟨U \ B, hVsub, hVopen, hxV⟩

theorem interior_closure_idempotent_seven {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  simp [Topology.interior_closure_idempotent]

theorem IsOpen.diff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hB : IsClosed (B : Set X)) :
    IsOpen (A \ B) := by
  simpa [Set.diff_eq] using hA.inter hB.isOpen_compl
